cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL

The paper deals with deep learning for visual recognition, specifically using web images as training data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a weakly supervised learning framework, which is a common topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of attention mechanisms is also a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the issue of noisy labels, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.MM, cs.IR, and cs.CL.
